<paragraph blockId="76.[164,1371,266,926]" pageId="76" pageNumber="676">one. Tail is shorter than head-body length and is white on the terminal part, but dark brown onbasal two-thirds. As with its congeners, skull has an elongated narrow mandible and there are only two lower molars; it has three upper molars, whereas the other members of genus have only two. Females bear two pairs of inguinal mammae.</paragraph>
